Note#4:
Epigraph : If solitude succeed to grief,
Release from pain is no relief;
The vacant bosom’s wilderness
Might thank the pang that made it less.
We loathe what none are left to share &endash;
Even bliss &endash; `twere woe alone to bear. LORD BYRON

Note#2:
Source not listed : Me let the tender office long engage
To rock the cradle of reposing age;
With lenient arts extend a mother’s breath,
Make languor smile, and smooth the bed of death;
Explore the thought, explain the asking eye,
And keep awhile a parent from the sky!
